            <h3>Growth</h3>
            <div class="price">$3,000 <span>SGD/mo</span></div>
            <p class="pricing-desc">For established cafes and small chains.</p>
            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>SEO + Google Ads + IG/TikTok</li>
              <li>Coffee and food photography direction</li>
              <li>GCLID walk-in and booking tracking</li>
              <li>Catchment-area landing pages</li>
              <li>Bi-weekly reporting</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
          </div>
          <div class="pricing-card reveal reveal-d3">
            <h3>Enterprise</h3>
            <div class="price">$5,500+ <span>SGD/mo</span></div>
            <p class="pricing-desc">For multi-outlet cafe groups and premium concepts.</p>
            <ul class="pricing-features">
              <li>Full 6-channel coverage</li>
              <li>Dedicated strategist</li>
              <li>Video production for Reels &amp; TikTok</li>
              <li>Brand refresh / in-store collateral</li>
              <li>Weekly reporting &amp; strategy calls</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-secondary">Let's Talk</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="section faq-section" id="faq" style="background: var(--bg-alt);" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about cafe marketing in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2><span class="highlight">Cafe</span> Marketing — Questions <span class="highlight">Answered</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How much does cafe marketing cost in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Cafe marketing in Singapore starts at S$1,800/month for essential single-channel work (typically Google Business Profile plus SEO or social content). Growth packages at S$3,000/month combine SEO, Google Ads, and IG/TikTok with coffee and food photography direction. Enterprise packages at S$5,500+/month add video production, brand refresh, and a dedicated strategist for multi-outlet cafe groups.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Why is Instagram so important for cafe marketing?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Singapore cafe-goers — especially the brunch and specialty coffee crowd — discover most new spots on IG Reels and TikTok before ever Googling. Aesthetic interior, latte art, and signature dish content drive the first visit. The cafes filling tables aren't necessarily the ones with the best espresso — they're the ones with consistent branded social content and UGC the audience actually shares.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
          <summary>What's the buyer journey for a cafe-goer in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Five stages: Discover (IG Reels, TikTok, cafe-hopping blogs, friend recs) → Choose (Google Maps three-pack, reviews, ChatGPT/AI search, Burpple) → First Visit (photos, vibe, menu convert intent) → Return (loyalty driven by experience, content, weekly regulars) → Advocate (UGC posts, Google reviews, IG stories). Cafe marketing has to show up at every stage — especially Discover and Choose, where most cafes lose to better-photographed competitors.</p></div>
        </details>
